<%= content_tag( 'h1', 'About this application' ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "This application is based on data collated by #{link_to( 'David Beamish', 'https://twitter.com/clerkly' )}. The information was originally published at #{link_to( 'United Kingdom peerage creations 1801 to 2020: peerages.info', 'http://peerages.info/' )}.".html_safe ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "Whilst the data at peerages.info is peerage centric, we have decided to normalise people from the peerages they were granted. This has been done on the assumption that every record sharing the same set of forenames, surname, date of birth, date of death - where present - and gender represents the same person. This logic has been checked and cleared by David Beamish." ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "Normalising people allows us to give each person an identifier - and a URL - meaning we can link to them and link them to other data sets. For example: it makes it possible to publish claims of equivalence to and from people identified by the #{link_to( 'Rush data', 'https://membersafter1832.historyofparliamentonline.org/' )} and #{link_to( 'Wikidata', 'https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Wikidata:Main_Page')}.".html_safe ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "In normalising people, we have created a table called 'peerage holdings' which allows us to describe multiple people holding the same peerage over time. As yet we do not have data for this and are only capturing persons first holding a peerage." ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'h2', 'Questions' ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "There are a number of questions which remain unanswered:" ) %>
<ol>
	<%= content_tag( 'li', "The source data has peerages having subsidiary titles. This doesn't work for titles with different special remainders where the peerages might part company as the different titles move down different lines of inheritance. See peerages under #{link_to( 'this letters patent', 'http://peerages.herokuapp.com/letters-patent/2727' )} for example. peerages.info has 'a subsidiary peerage created by the same letters patent as a higher-ranking peerage'. Are parent and subsidiary peerages created by the same letters patent or different letters patent issued on the same day?".html_safe ) %>
	
	<%= content_tag( 'li', "All subsidiary peerages have the same date for issue of letters patent as their parent peerage, except for the current #{link_to( 'Duke of Cambridge', peerage_show_url( :peerage => 2740 ) )} whose main peerage has a letters patent date of 26/05/2011, with two subsidiary titles - the #{link_to( 'Earl of Strathearn', peerage_show_url( :peerage => 3106 ) )} and #{link_to( 'Lord Carrickfergus', peerage_show_url( :peerage => 3099 ) )} - having a letters patent date of 29/04/2011. We have checked the London Gazette and found a single announcement. For now, we have assumed incorrect dates on the subsidiaries and combined them into the same letters patent as the 'parent' peerage. Is this a data entry error or can there be a gap between issuing of parent and subsidiary peerages?".html_safe ) %>
	
	<%= content_tag( 'li', "What is the number attribute on announcements?" ) %>
	
	<%= content_tag( 'li', "Is it possible for peerages of different types to be created in the same letters patent?" ) %>
	
	<%= content_tag( 'li', "Is there ever an announcement upon inheritance of a peerage?" ) %>
	
	<%= content_tag( 'li', "Assuming letters patent are what we think they are, should they hang off a peerage - as at present - or decorate a holding?" ) %>
	
	<%= content_tag( 'li', "#{link_to( 'Category 5 of special remainders', special_remainder_show_url( :special_remainder => 5 ) )} implies peerages grouped have special remainders but is used to group peerages with subsidiary titles with special remainders. Should this category exist?".html_safe ) %>
	
	<%= content_tag( 'li', "Some peerages point to announcements of a type that are not present in the data. Can we create these?" ) %>
</ol>
